        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(autoreview): simplify helper paths in SKILL.md",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR cleans up `skills/autoreview/SKILL.md` by removing the hardcoded helper path and simplifying how the autoreview scripts are referenced.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\n\r\nThe SKILL.md repeated helper paths in multiple places. Setting them once makes it easier and safer for agents to use the correct autoreview command consistently.\r\n\r\nAlso, there was a personal local path in the SKILL.md (closes https://github.com/openclaw/agent-skills/issues/12):\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview\r\n```\r\n\r\n## What Changed\r\n\r\n- Added a simple `## Skill Path (Bash)` section\r\n- Sets `AUTOREVIEW` and `AUTOREVIEW_HARNESS` once to use those variables throughout the bash examples\r\n- Keeps project-local and global skill setups clear\r\n- Simplifies the `## Helper` section so it reuses the variables instead of repeating paths\r\n- Removes personal path examples",
        "branch": "fix/paths",
